# Pure Java Migration - CreateClaim Procedure

Analyzing the RPG procedure `CreateClaim`, I will generate a complete Pure Java application with layered architecture. This procedure processes claim position data from HSGPSLF3, aggregates it by failure number, and creates claim failures in HSG73PF, then updates the claim header in HSG71PF.

**Key Business Logic:**
- Read position data (HSGPSLF3) grouped by failure number
- Aggregate material/labor/special values per failure
- Extract maintenance flag, groups, part numbers, and text lines
- Create failure records (HSG73PF) via `createFail` procedure
- Update claim header status (HSG71PF) to status 3
- Unlock both files after processing

**Architecture:**
- 3 entities (Claim, ClaimError, ClaimPosition) mapping 104 columns
- Repositories with Spring Data JPA
- Service layer with stateless business logic
- DTOs using Java Records
- Enums for status codes and record types

